Untitled movement,recorders (2), continuo,C major (GB Cfm MU.MS.261, p. 69)
For two treble instruments (range F'-F''', probably recorders) and bass (b), HWV 405 (where thay are said to be flutes).
Editorial title.
Holograph manuscript in ink. The movement on p. 65 is probably in another hand; the clefs on p. 72 and 75 are probably in another hand.
Watermark:  [Italian paper] (Burrows A40)
Contents:
p. 69. [Movement for 2 recorders and bass in C major / anonymous (possibly not in Handel's hand)] -- p. 70. [Allegro for 2 recorders without bass in F major, HWV 405, no. 1] -- p. 73-74. Grave [for 2 recorders and bass in D minor, HWV 405 no. 2] -- p. 74-76.[Allegro for 2 recorders and bass in F major, HWV 405, no. 3]
